    "body": "<!--To help us understand and resolve your issue, please fill out the form to the best of your ability. Feel free to delete the sections that do not apply.-->\r\n\r\nHi,\r\n\r\nI'm having trouble with grdtrack using the -nl flag, where I get an Abort trap. It only occurs with -nl, and not with any of the other interpolation schemes. The flag works using GMT6.1.1, but not with GMT6.3.0. \r\n\r\n<!-- Please be as detailed as you can when describing an issue. The more information we have, the easier it will be for us to track this down. -->\r\n\r\n**Full script that generated the error**\r\n\r\n<!-- It helps a lot if you share any data files required to run your script. You can drag-and-drop them here or paste a link to Dropbox/GoogleDrive/etc. -->\r\n\r\n```\r\ngmt grdtrack input.txt -fg -nl GlobSed-v2.nc -V > output.txt\r\n```\r\nHere, `input.txt` contains coordinates in 2\u00b0 increments (also failed at 1\u00b0 and 0.1\u00b0), e.g.\r\n-180 -90\r\n-178 -90\r\n-176 -90\r\n-174 -90\r\n-172 -90\r\n-170 -90\r\netc\r\n\r\nand `GlobSed-v2.nc` is global sediment thickness (also fails with ETOPO).\r\n\r\n**Full error message**\r\n\r\n<!-- Tip: you'll get more detailed error messages if you add -Vd to your gmt commands. -->\r\n\r\n```\r\nAssertion failed: (node < G->header->size), function gmt_bcr_get_z, file gmt_bcr.c, line 297.\r\nAbort trap: 6\r\n```\r\n\r\n**System information**\r\n\r\n* Operating system: macOS Monterey 12.2\r\n* GMT version: 6.3.0\r\n\r\nAny help would be greatly appreciated!",
