        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "There are two problems that this example illustrates:\r\n\r\n1. GMT defaults to pixel registration for remote grids.  This is in general fine, but for **grdtrack** it poses a problem.  Input points beyond the s/n node boundaries (which are |90-0.5*yinc|) are \"outside the grid\" and hence needs a boundary pad even for bilinear sampling.  For remote grids used in **grdtrack** I think we should default to gridline registration unless the user specifies a registration.\r\n2. The crash I can fix by requiring a boundary pad for pixel grids.\r\n\r\n@nickywright, I assume GlobSed-v2.nc is a pixel-registered global grid?\r\n",
            "created_at": "2022-02-08T18:58:06Z",
