        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Hi @PaulWessel, [GlobSed-v2.nc](https://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/mgg/sedthick/) is gridline registered:\r\n\r\noutput from grdinfo:\r\n```\r\nGlobSed-v2.nc: Title: Produced by grdmath\r\nGlobSed-v2.nc: Command: grdclip GlobSed_v2.nc -Sb0/0 -GGlobSed-v2.nc\r\nGlobSed-v2.nc: Remark:\r\nGlobSed-v2.nc: Gridline node registration ued [Geographic grid]\r\nGlobSed-v2.nc: Grid file format: nf = GMT netCDF format (32-bit float), CF-1.7\r\nGlobSed-v2.nc: x_min: -180 x_max: 180 x_inc: 0.0833333333333 (5 min) name: longitude n_columns: 4321\r\nGlobSed-v2.nc: y_min: -90 y_max: 90 y_inc: 0.0833333333333 (5 min) name: latitude n_rows: 2161\r\nGlobSed-v2.nc: z_min: 0 z_max: 18333.6972656 name: z\r\nGlobSed-v2.nc: scale_factor: 1 add_offset: 0\r\nGlobSed-v2.nc: format: netCDF-4 chunk_size: 131,136 shuffle: on deflation_level: 3\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nI just compiled GMT from source (gmt version `6.4.0_d592d1a-dirty_2022.02.08`) and it still seems to be crashing, sorry!\r\n\r\n```\r\nERROR: Caught signal number 11 (Segmentation fault: 11) at\r\n0   libgmt.6.4.0.dylib                  0x000000010349e7a0 gmt_bcr_get_z + 368\r\n1   ???                                 0x00007f8ffab9f044 0x0 + 140256363540548\r\nStack backtrace:\r\n0   libgmt.6.4.0.dylib                  0x000000010358c828 sig_handler_unix + 216\r\n1   libsystem_platform.dylib            0x00007ff80288de2d _sigtramp + 29\r\n2   ???                                 0x000000000000000d 0x0 + 13\r\n3   libgmt.6.4.0.dylib                  0x00000001037b6cf5 grdtrack_sample_all_grids + 165\r\n4   libgmt.6.4.0.dylib                  0x00000001037b504f GMT_grdtrack + 21135\r\n5   libgmt.6.4.0.dylib                  0x000000010347d464 GMT_Call_Module + 2180\r\n6   gmt                                 0x0000000102de33b1 main + 1841\r\n7   dyld                                0x000000010694d4fe start + 462\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
